    # game/areas/oldpagos.rpy:401
    old "[oldpagos_fluff] She stands in the middle, in front of dozens of members of her tribe, though you’re still told to keep your distance. The signs of illness are carved in the exhausted faces of the elders and the children, but this is not the day of sadness - you’re greeted with triumphant shouts and applause. \n\n{color=#f6d6bd}Tertia{/color} turns out to be tall and skinny, holding a spear that would be too long for most, but suits her size. While her tribesfolk are wearing tunics and robes made of ibex fur or hemp, she has put on an impressive breastplate made of animal shell. She has short, dark hair, and while her skin is dark brown, you can tell there are others in her village who carry the blood of the Southerners. \n\nHer voice matches her cheerful brown eyes as she speaks in the name of her people. “We keep ye in our prayers, [pcname]! If we could, we would invite ye to a feast, but we need to keep our distance, at least till the end of winter. We’d like to reward ye, even if there’s naught that would make us even.” "
